Sentencas: Double perovskite La1.8Sr0.2CoFeO5+delta (DP-LSCF) is prepared by a modified sol-gel method and investigated as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs, 600-850 degrees C).
Titulo: Double perovskite La1.8Sr0.2CoFeO5+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The compound is characterised by a variety of techniques, including TG/DTA, X-ray diffraction, Raman spectroscopy, X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy and SEM-EDS.
Titulo: Double perovskite La1.8Sr0.2CoFeO5+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The formation of the double perovskite structure with rhombohedral symmetry after its calcination at 1000 degrees C for 6 h is revealed by X-ray diffraction.
Titulo: Double perovskite La1.8Sr0.2CoFeO5+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Excellent chemical compatibility with a Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (GDC) electrolyte is found.
Titulo: Double perovskite La1.8Sr0.2CoFeO5+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The double perovskite structure is confirmed by Raman and X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy.
Titulo: Double perovskite La1.8Sr0.2CoFeO5+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The partial substitution of Fe cations at the Co site affects the physical-chemical properties of DP-LSCF.
Titulo: Double perovskite La1.8Sr0.2CoFeO5+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Compared with other double perovskite materials based on Co, DP-LSCF shows a lower thermal expansion coefficient (19.4 x 10(-6) K-1).
Titulo: Double perovskite La1.8Sr0.2CoFeO5+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The compound exhibits semiconductor behaviour and an area specific resistance of 0.42 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C when GDC is employed as the electrolyte.
Titulo: Double perovskite La1.8Sr0.2CoFeO5+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results suggest that DP-LSCF is a promising cathode material for IT-SOFC applications.
Titulo: Double perovskite La1.8Sr0.2CoFeO5+δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
